---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Alejandro Berrizbeitia"
  description="Narratives in numbers. Semantic layers for human and machine analysts — told in narratives, grounded in numbers."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-14 md:py-20">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-midnight dark:text-silver md:text-4xl">
      Narratives in numbers.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-3 font-serif text-lg text-midnight/90 dark:text-silver/90 md:text-xl">
      Semantic layers for human and machine analysts — told in narratives, grounded in numbers.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-muted dark:text-silver">
      I build the layer between raw data and the people (and agents) who need answers from it. Senior
      Data Analyst at Kit, focused on the semantic layer as the source-of-truth model behind
      dashboards, notebooks, and AI agents. I design semantic models, apply causal inference where
      dashboards fall short, and ship AI agent skills that encode that judgment for reuse. Public
      work lives in <code class="rounded bg-silver/25 px-1 py-0.5 text-sm text-midnight dark:text-ink-dark"
        >intelligence-layer</code
      > and <code class="rounded bg-silver/25 px-1 py-0.5 text-sm text-midnight dark:text-ink-dark"
        >agent-skills</code
      >. MBA. OKR practitioner. Trilingual: English, Spanish, French. Based in Paris.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-16 space-y-14">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-midnight dark:text-silver">Building</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-ink-muted dark:text-silver">
          Repositories and side projects indexed from the same machine-readable list as the public
          hub. Cards, status, and links live on the dedicated page.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          <a
            href="/building/"
            class="font-medium text-midnight underline decoration-silver decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-midnight dark:text-silver dark:hover:text-ink-dark"
          >
            View building →
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-midnight dark:text-silver">Writing</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-ink-muted dark:text-silver">
          Newsletter issues and long-form pieces. The newsletter is <cite class="not-italic"
            >The Intelligence Layer</cite
          >; essays ship as MDX on this site when published.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          <a
            href="/writing/"
            class="font-medium text-midnight underline decoration-silver decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-midnight dark:text-silver dark:hover:text-ink-dark"
          >
            View writing →
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-midnight dark:text-silver">Reading</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-ink-muted dark:text-silver">
          Perpetually reading. When <em>biblioscope</em> ships, literary analytics and reading logs
          will sit there; until then, see <a href="/building/" class="text-midnight underline dark:text-silver"
            >Building</a
          > for project status.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
